Subject: leucophore [CEPH:0000284]
Value: leucophore

Subject: leucophore [CEPH:0001077]
Value: leucophore

Subject: accessory gland complex [CEPH:0000004]
Value: The glandular complex in cirrates that forms sperm packets and is a counterpart of the spermatophore-forming complex of other cephalopods.

Subject: armature of the arms [CEPH:0000018]
Value: The grappling structures on the oral surfaces the arms and tentacles, including both suckers and hooks.

Subject: a-seriation [CEPH:0000019]
Value: Type of cusp arrangement on the rachadian tooth of the radula: multiple cusps seem to move laterally when viewing successive rachadian teeth from adjacent rows.

Subject: basal shelf [CEPH:0000021]
Value: See cirrate shell terminology.

Subject: branchial heart [CEPH:0000032]
Value: A pulsating gland at the base of the gill and through which the afferent blood to the gills flows. It contributes to the blood flow through the gill but also is the site of hemocyanin (the blood respiratory pigment) synthesis.

Subject: carpus [CEPH:0000053]
Value: The region of the tentacle that contains the carpal locking-apparatus

Subject: cirrate male reproductive system [CEPH:0000063]
Value: The male reproductive tract of cirrates does not make typical spermatophores. As a result, the tract differs greatly from that of other coleoid cephalopods.

Subject: cirrate octopod measurements [CEPH:0000064]
Value: Measurements used in describing cirrates differ somewhat from other cephalopods.

Subject: dorsal mantle cavity [CEPH:0000093]
Value: Dorsal portion of the mantle cavity that completely surrounds the viscera in octopods. In decapodiforms and Vampyroteuthis the viscera are fused to the mantle and shell dorsally and the mantle cavity lies lateral and ventral to the viscera.

Subject: eyelid sinus [CEPH:0000104]
Value: Indentation, often complex, of the anterior margin of the eyelid.

Subject: fin attachment [CEPH:0000106]
Value: A fin attaches to the shell, the mantle, the opposite fin or some combination of these.

Subject: fin cartilage [CEPH:0000107]
Value: Cartilage associated with the fins of all fin-bearing cephalopods.

Subject: fin length [CEPH:0000108]
Value: This measurement varies in different major taxa.

Subject: fin position [CEPH:0000110]
Value: Fins are located anterior to the termination of the muscular mantle (subterminal position) or mostly posterior to it (terminal position) or somewhere inbetween.

Subject: fin shape [CEPH:0000111]
Value: Fins are classified, somewhat arbitrarily, by their shape as Sagittate, Rhomboid, Circular/Elliptical, Lanceolate, Ear-shaped, Ribbed, Lobate or skirt-like.

Subject: half-orange gill [CEPH:0000126]
Value: Gills of some cirrate octopods with broad primary lamellae whose arrangement looks similar to half of an orange.

Subject: lateral funnel adductor muscle [CEPH:0000147]
Value: Muscles that support the lateral attachment of the funnel to the head.

Subject: locking-apparatus of tentacular stalk [CEPH:0000156]
Value: Continuation of the carpal locking apparatus down the oral face of the tentacular stalk.

Subject: mantle septum [CEPH:0000161]
Value: A anteroposterior septum that connects the mantle wall with the visceral sac along the midline in the ventral mantle cavity. The ventral mantle artery runs along the anterior end of this septum.

Subject: nuchal region [CEPH:0000180]
Value: The posterodorsal region of the head and the area immediately posterior to it.

Subject: oviducal gland [CEPH:0000193]
Value: Gland surrounding the end of the primary oviduct and responsible for secreting some of the external coatings over spawned eggs or, in incirrates, the cement at the base of the chorion stalk . In octopods it also acts as a spermatheca, and is located around the apparent middle of the oviduct. However, the "distal oviduct" is actually an extension of the oviducal gland.

Subject: photophore location [CEPH:0000199]
Value: Photophores are found in nearly any location in some squid. However, certain locations are the most common.

Subject: posterior buccal lobe [CEPH:0000204]
Value: A fused pair of lobes that are the anterior-most lobes of the supraesophageal mass of the brain of decapodiforms but is incorporated into the anterior portion of the supraesophageal mass behind the superior buccal lobes in most octopodiforms.

Subject: pseudomorph [CEPH:0000211]
Value: A mass of ink and mucous that roughly has the dimensions of the cephalopod that secreted it.

Subject: rostrum [CEPH:0000217]
Value: Portion of the gladius that extends posteriorly or posterodorsally from the conus. A distnct rostrum is found only in the Onychoteuthidae, Ancistrocheiridae, Lampadioteuthinae and Vampyroteuthidae.

Subject: saddle [CEPH:0000218]
Value: The region of the shell of cirrates connecting the lateral wings.

Subject: sagittate fin [CEPH:0000220]
Value: The most common fin-shape in squids with anterior free fin-lobes, a relatively sharp lateral angle and posterior elongation. See fin shapes.

Subject: scales and tubercule [CEPH:0000221]
Value: The skin of the mantle contains scales, tubercules and warts in various species.

Subject: secondary eyelid [CEPH:0000223]
Value: An eyelid that covers the ventral part of the cornea.

Subject: sucker series [CEPH:0000249]
Value: The longitudinal rows of suckers on the arms or tentacles of decapodiforms. Series (= longitudinal rows) contrasts with rows (= transverse rows) in describing sucker arrangement. In octopodiforms, sucker "series" is generally synonymous with "rows", the "longitudinal" component of the term is implied. Suckers can form distinct, regular series or indistinct, irregular series.

Subject: tentacle absence [CEPH:0000257]
Value: Tentacles can be absent because the species lacks tentacles, they are accidentally lost during capture, or they are naturally lost at sexual maturity.

Subject: funnel component of funnel-mantle locking apparatus [CEPH:0001051]
mantle component of funnel-mantle locking apparatus [CEPH:0001052]
marginal epithelial layer of the gladius [CEPH:0001074]
efferent vein [CEPH:0000094]
Value: vein carrying blood away from an organ.

Subject: efferent nerve [CEPH:0000095]
Value: nerve carring impulses away from the brain or specific ganglia.

Subject: mantle length [CEPH:0000160]
Value: (ML) - The standard measure of length in coleoid cephalopods. In decapodiforms ML is measured along the dorsal midline from the mantle margin to the posterior tip of the body, excluding long tails. In octopodiforms ML is measured from a line joining the midpoint of the eyes rather than the anterior mantle margin since the latter is obscured by the head/mantle fusion.

Subject: semicrescent plate [CEPH:0000227]
Value: (arm suckers) - A semicrescent plate on the proximal margin of the inner sucker arm rings of the loliginid squid Uroteuthis.

Subject: wing [CEPH:0000283]
Value: (shell) - Lateral limbs of the shell of cirrate octopods

Subject: anal photophore [CEPH:0000304]
Value: photophore at side of anus

Subject: buccal membrane support [CEPH:0000310]
Value: longitudinal muscular rod fused with buccal membrane

Subject: bullet-shaped mantle [CEPH:0001001]
Value: posteriorly blunt rather than broad body (mantle) common in larval cephalopods

Subject: dorsal shield [CEPH:0001035]
Value: hard calcareous dorsal surface of the cuttlebone

Subject: epirenal body [CEPH:0001036]
Value: glandular structures of unknown function which lie on either side of the renal papillae

Subject: umbilicus [CEPH:0001039]
Value: the central core of the chambered Nautilus shell, representing the juvenile shell with its initial coils

Subject: shell apex [CEPH:0001050]
Value: the tip of the mollusc shell of a gastropod, scaphopod, or cephalopod mollusc.

Subject: iteroparous [CEPH:0001067]
Value: characterized by multiple reproductive cycles over the course of its lifetime
